---
import Divider from "../../components/Divider.astro";
import PageLink from "../../components/PageLink.astro";
import DarkLayout from "../../layouts/DarkLayout.astro";
import "../../styles/base.scss";
---

<DarkLayout>
  <header>
    <h1>Blog</h1>
  </header>
  <Divider />

  <section id="blog-posts">
    <div class="blog-posts-wrapper" id="designdiscovery">
      <h3>Navigating the Tech Landscape</h3>
      <div class="blog-post">
        <div class="left">
         <img src="/images/blog/navigating.jpg" alt="Navigating the Tech Cover art" />
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <p>
            In the fast-paced world of technology, staying ahead of the curve is not just a competitive
            advantage but a necessity. As a technical leader, you're undoubtedly aware of the challenges
            in keeping your team informed about the latest tools, platforms, and trends. This is where the
            concept of a Technology Radar comes into play.
          </p>
          <div class="bottom">
            <PageLink href="/blog/navigating_the_tech_landscape" text="Read more" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <Divider />
    </div>
    <div class="blog-posts-wrapper" id="designdiscovery">
      <h3>Delusion of Value</h3>
      <div class="blog-post">
        <div class="left">
         <img src="/images/blog/delusion.jpg" alt="Delusion of Value Cover art" />
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <p>
            Human nature often leans toward pretension and ego. We have a tendency to
            perceive ourselves through the distorted reflections of status, unaware that we are
            like figures in a funhouse mirror â€” a narrative as ancient as our existence.
            Our societal validation often hinges on materialistic possessions rather than profound ideas.
            We tend to overlook the wisdom encapsulated in the saying "Clothes don't make the man".
          </p>
          <div class="bottom">
            <PageLink href="/blog/delusion_of_value" text="Read more" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <Divider />
    </div>
    <div class="blog-posts-wrapper" id="designdiscovery">
      <h3>Insights into Collaborating with a Software House for Product Development</h3>
      <div class="blog-post">
        <div class="left">
         <img src="/images/blog/product-studio.jpg" alt="Delusion of Value Cover art" />
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <p>
            In this article we explore the nuances of selecting the optimal product development approach,
            emphasizing the essential traits to seek for a successful product development journey.
            A perspective shared by of seasoned expert, leading development teams for 20 years at companies
            like Allegro, home.pl and Shoper.
          </p>
          <div class="bottom">
            <PageLink href="/blog/insights_into_collaborating" text="Read more" />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <Divider />
    </div>    
  </section>
</DarkLayout>

<style lang="scss" is:global>
  @use "@/styles/helpers" as *;

  main {
    h1 {
      @include typography(main-header);
      color: var(--main-text);
      line-height: 1.15;
    }

    header {
      display: flex;
      flex-flow: column;
      gap: var(--spacing-m);
      padding-top: var(--spacing-xl);

      @include media-breakpoint-up(xl) {
        flex-flow: row wrap;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: flex-start;
      }

      & > a {
        display: block;
        @include media-breakpoint-up(xl) {
          margin-left: auto;
        }
      }
    }
    & > header {
      display: flex;
      flex-flow: column;
      gap: var(--spacing-m);
      padding-top: var(--spacing-xl);

      @include media-breakpoint-up(xl) {
        flex-flow: row wrap;
      }

      & > a {
        display: block;
        @include media-breakpoint-up(xl) {
          margin-left: auto;
        }
      }
    }
  }

  #blog-posts {
    display: flex;
    flex-flow: column;
    row-gap: var(--spacing-xl);
    padding-top: var(--spacing-xll);

    & > h2 {
      @include typography(section-title);
      color: var(--main-text);
      line-height: 1.5;
    }

    .blog-posts-wrapper {
      width: 100%;
      display: flex;
      flex-flow: column;
      row-gap: 48px;

      & > h3 {
        grid-row: 1;
        grid-column: 1 / 2;
        @include typography(sub-header);
        color: var(--main-text);
      }

      & > .blog-post {
        display: grid;
        width: 100%;
        column-gap: 30px;
        align-items: start;
        justify-content: start;
        grid-template-rows: auto auto;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr;

        @include media-breakpoint-down(lg) {
          row-gap: var(--spacing-xl);
        }

        @include media-breakpoint-up(lg) {
          grid-template-rows: auto;
          grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        }

        & > .left {
          grid-row: 1;
          grid-column: 1 / 2;
          @include media-breakpoint-up(lg) {
            grid-row: 1;
            grid-column: 1 / 2;
          }

          p {
            @include typography(paragraph);
            color: var(--main-text);
          }

          img {
            width: 100%;
            height: auto;
            object-fit: cover;
          }
        }

        & > .right {
          display: flex;
          flex-flow: column;
          row-gap: var(--spacing-s);

          grid-row: 2;
          grid-column: 1 / 2;

          @include media-breakpoint-up(lg) {
            grid-row: 1;
            grid-column: 2 / 3;
          }

          p,
          li {
            @include typography(label);
            color: var(--main-text);
          }

          ul {
            list-style: none;
            padding: 0;
            margin: 0;
            padding-left: 20px;

            li {
              position: relative;
              &::before {
                content: "\2022";
                display: block;
                position: absolute;
                left: -20px;
                top: 0;
              }
            }
          }

          & > .bottom {
            display: flex;
            flex-flow: row nowrap;
            align-items: center;
            justify-content: flex-end;
            width: 100%;
            user-select: none;
            padding-top: 20px;
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
</style>
